# CrossCheck.com — Full-Stack Implementation Plan
> PRD v1.0 | Prepared by: Sri, Rishi, Arkesh, Likith | Engineering Review: April 2026

---

## Executive Engineering Summary

CrossCheck.com is a **dual-sided AI platform** (Employee + Employer) built with React/TypeScript on the front, FastAPI on the back, and a suite of **in-house ML models** (no external LLMs). The plan below translates every PRD requirement into concrete engineering tasks, file structures, API contracts, and deployment steps across **7 milestones**.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **No external LLMs allowed.** Every AI capability must be trained in-house on Kaggle datasets. This is architecturally challenging — see Section 5 (AI Strategy) for the model pipeline plan and dataset recommendations. Team must confirm Kaggle dataset licenses before M3.

> [!WARNING]
> **Razorpay integration** — The PRD is ambiguous on Pro tier pricing model: one-time purchase vs. monthly subscription. This affects DB schema (payments table structure), webhook logic, and the employer portal. **Decision required before M1 ends.**

> [!WARNING]
> **Employer PII Consent Trigger** — The PRD states employers cannot see candidate PII "without consent" but doesn't define the consent mechanism. This must be designed before M6 (Employer Portal). Options: (a) Candidate opts-in per-job, (b) Candidate gives blanket opt-in during onboarding. **Decision required before M6.**

> [!CAUTION]
> **Voice Data Storage** — Audio recordings require explicit GDPR/DPDP consent and secure encrypted storage. The PRD leaves this open (MinIO vs. Antigravity object store). **Decide before M4.** This impacts the backend file-handling architecture significantly.

