## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q1 — Razorpay pricing model**: Is Pro tier a one-time purchase (₹X) or monthly subscription? This affects the payments table, webhook logic, and tier expiry handling. Please confirm before M1 ends.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q2 — GitHub OAuth**: GitHub API's unauthenticated rate limit is 60 requests/hour — far too low for production. Pro users will need to authorize CrossCheck's GitHub OAuth app to provide a user token. Is the team okay with this additional OAuth step for Pro users?

> [!WARNING]
> **Q3 — AI retraining trigger**: Will model retraining be triggered manually by an admin (simpler, safer) or automatically when new data crosses a threshold? Manual is strongly recommended for v1.0 to prevent model drift in production.

> [!WARNING]
> **Q4 — Voice storage**: MinIO (self-hosted on Antigravity) vs. Supabase Storage (simpler, S3-compatible)? If MinIO, we need an additional Docker container and bucket lifecycle policies. Recommend **Supabase Storage** for v1.0 to reduce ops complexity.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q5 — DPDP / GDPR**: Is CrossCheck India-first? If yes, DPDP Act 2023 requires a Data Privacy Notice, explicit consent for each data category (CV, voice, onboarding answers), and a Data Fiduciary registration. This must be scoped before M1.

> [!WARNING]
> **Q6 — Whisper-small compute**: Running Whisper-small in real-time per voice answer requires a GPU or a beefy CPU. Has the Antigravity Cloud environment been sized for this? Recommend: dedicated Whisper container with async job queue (Redis + Celery) to prevent blocking API responses.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q7 — Mobile priority**: Should mobile (React Native/Expo) be built in parallel with web (recommended), or as Phase 2 after web is complete? This significantly affects the team structure and timeline.

